sentences: Steven Eugene Grove (born November 27, 1962), better known as Euge Groove, is an American  smooth jazz saxophonist.
Born in Hagerstown, Maryland, he graduated from the University of Miami School of Music in 1984.
Grove did not record his first solo album until 2000.

Grove adopted the name Euge Groove; initially presumed to be coined by fans who saw him perform in Europe, Grove later indicated in an interview on XM Radio in 2006 that his mother-in-law conceived the idea for his stage name.
Albums include: S7ven Large (2011), Born 2 Groove (2006), Livin' Large (2004) and Play Date (2002).

In 2008 he went on tour with Tina Turner.
He has a sax solo on their No. 1 hit "Seasons Change," and another on their 1993 hit "I'll Never Get Over You (Getting Over Me)."
Euge Groove's best-known solo hits include "Sneak a Peek," "Slam Dunk," "Rewind," "Don't Let Me Be Lonely Tonight," "Livin' Large" and "XXL."
He has recently released another album, titled "Sunday Morning."
